body:
Sure, here's a sample notification email in HTML format:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Merchandise Hold Notification</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin: 20px;
        }
       .container {
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #333;
        }
        p {
            color: #666;
        }
       .action {
            margin-top: 20px;
            color: #007bff;
            text-decoration: underline;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Merchandise Hold Notification</h1>
        <p>Dear valued customer,</p>
        <p>We regret to inform you that your merchandise has been placed on hold due to unpaid fees. To resolve this issue and release your merchandise, please follow these steps:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Log in to your account on our website.</li>
            <li>Navigate to the "Payment" or "Fees" section.</li>
            <li>Locate and click on the "Unpaid Fees" option.</li>
            <li>Review the outstanding fees and select the method of payment you prefer.</li>
            <li>Complete the payment process.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>Once the fees have been paid, your merchandise will be released and you will receive a confirmation email.</p>
        <p>If you have any questions or need further assistance, please don't hesitate to contact our customer support at <a href="mailto:customer.support@example.com">customer.support@example.com</a> or call us at (123) 456-7890.</p>
        <p>Thank you for your prompt attention to this matter.</p>
        <p>Best regards,</p>
        <p>Your Company Name</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```

Replace the placeholder information like email address and phone number with the actual details relevant to your company.

Sure, here is an example of an HTML email to notify a recipient about a parcel retention due to outstanding payments:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Parcel Retention Notice</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }
       .container {
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            background-color: #ffffff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        h1 {
            color: #333333;
        }
        p {
            color: #666666;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
       .cta-button {
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            text-align: center;
            text-decoration: none;
            display: inline-block;
            font-size: 16px;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
       .cta-button:hover {
            background-color: #45a049;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Important: Your Parcel is Retained Due to Outstanding Payments</h1>
        <p>Dear [Recipient's Name],</p>
        <p>We regret to inform you that your parcel has been retained due to outstanding payments on your account. To ensure we can deliver your package promptly, please complete the payment process at your earliest convenience.</p>
        <p>Your parcel will remain in our retention facility until the payment is received and processed.</p>
        <p>Thank you for your prompt attention to this matter.</p>
        <p>Best regards,<br>Your Company Name</p>
        <a href="https://www.yourcompany.com/payments" class="cta-button">Complete Your Payment</a>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```

This HTML email includes a heading, a personalized message, a call-to-action button, and styles to make it look clean and professional. Adjust the placeholders (e.g., `[Recipient's Name]`, `https://www.yourcompany.com/payments`) to fit the actual details of your situation.
